## Regex

Regular Expressions (aka regex) are a text pattern matching tool build into many programming languages and unix utilities.

The are made up of the recursive combination of 3 elements

  - Atomic Matches
    - The simplest expressions. They match a single character.
  - Sequences
    - The sequencial combination of 2 regular expression
  - Alternation
    - Will match if either of the sub expressions are matched
